arguments.prompt:
You are implementing a Blazor Web App for a logistics company that tracks shipments. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-8a948b3ad797449a85a13be4c1c7be50/ShipmentTracker/` using `dotnet new blazor -int Auto -ai -au Individual`.

The solution has two projects:
- `ShipmentTracker` (server) — hosts app, APIs, EF Core, Identity
- `ShipmentTracker.Client` (WebAssembly) — all interactive UI components

**Architecture rules for Auto Global mode:**
- All interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Interactive components cannot access DbContext directly — must use HTTP APIs
- Define service interfaces in `.Client`, implement with HttpClient there, and implement with direct DB access in the server project
- Register matching services in both Program.cs files
- Don't add `@rendermode` to individual pages — global mode is already configured in App.razor

## Requirements

1. **Dispatchers** view a list of shipments with status and destination
2. **Customers** check their shipment status and estimated delivery
3. **Authentication** — staff and customers authenticate with individual accounts (already scaffolded with Identity)

## Implementation Tasks

### 1. Create the Shipment data model

In the server project `ShipmentTracker/Data/`, create a `Shipment.cs` model:

```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public ShipmentStatus Status { get; set; }
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? CustomerEmail { get; set; }
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}

public enum ShipmentStatus
{
    Pending,
    PickedUp,
    InTransit,
    OutForDelivery,
    Delivered,
    Exception
}
```

### 2. Add Shipment to ApplicationDbContext

Edit `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to add:
```csharp
public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
```

### 3. Create shared DTOs in the Client project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentDto.cs`:

```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Status { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public DateTime CreatedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime? EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? CustomerEmail { get; set; }
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}
```

### 4. Create a service interface in the Client project

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:

```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string email);
    Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
    Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, string status);
}
```

Make sure to add the using for `ShipmentTracker.Client.Models`.

### 5. Implement the client-side service (uses HttpClient)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:

```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient http) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments") ?? [];

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto?>($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string email)
        => await http.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>($"api/shipments/customer/{Uri.EscapeDataString(email)}") ?? [];

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await http.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>() ?? shipment;
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, string status)
    {
        var response = await http.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{id}/status", new { Status = status });
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
    }
}
```

### 6. Implement server-side service (uses DbContext directly)

Create `ShipmentTracker/Services/ShipmentServerService.cs`:

```csharp
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;
using ShipmentTracker.Data;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Services;

public class ShipmentServerService(ApplicationDbContext db) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
        => await db.Shipments.Select(s => ToDto(s)).ToListAsync();

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
        => await db.Shipments.Where(s => s.TrackingNumber == trackingNumber).Select(s => ToDto(s)).FirstOrDefaultAsync();

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(string email)
        => await db.Shipments.Where(s => s.CustomerEmail == email).Select(s => ToDto(s)).ToListAsync();

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto dto)
    {
        var shipment = new Shipment
        {
            TrackingNumber = dto.TrackingNumber,
            Origin = dto.Origin,
            Destination = dto.Destination,
            Status = Enum.Parse<ShipmentStatus>(dto.Status),
            CreatedDate = DateTime.UtcNow,
            EstimatedDelivery = dto.EstimatedDelivery,
            CustomerEmail = dto.CustomerEmail,
            Notes = dto.Notes
        };
        db.Shipments.Add(shipment);
        await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        return ToDto(shipment);
    }

    public async Task UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(int id, string status)
    {
        var shipment = await db.Shipments.FindAsync(id);
        if (shipment is not null)
        {
            shipment.Status = Enum.Parse<ShipmentStatus>(status);
            await db.SaveChangesAsync();
        }
    }

    private static ShipmentDto ToDto(Shipment s) => new()
    {
        Id = s.Id,
        TrackingNumber = s.TrackingNumber,
        Origin = s.Origin,
        Destination = s.Destination,
        Status = s.Status.ToString(),
        CreatedDate = s.CreatedDate,
        EstimatedDelivery = s.EstimatedDelivery,
        CustomerEmail = s.CustomerEmail,
        Notes = s.Notes
    };
}
```

### 7. Add API endpoints to server Program.cs

After `app.MapAdditionalIdentityEndpoints();` in `ShipmentTracker/Program.cs`, add these API endpoints. Also add the required `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;` and service registration.

Before `var app = builder.Build();`, add:
```csharp
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentServerService>();
```

Also add `using ShipmentTracker.Services;` and `using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;` at the top.

After `app.MapAdditionalIdentityEndpoints();`, add:
```csharp
// Shipment API endpoints
var shipments = app.MapGroup("api/shipments").RequireAuthorization();

shipments.MapGet("/", async (IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetAllShipmentsAsync()));

shipments.MapGet("/track/{trackingNumber}", async (string trackingNumber, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    var shipment = await service.GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(trackingNumber);
    return shipment is not null ? Results.Ok(shipment) : Results.NotFound();
});

shipments.MapGet("/customer/{email}", async (string email, IShipmentService service) =>
    Results.Ok(await service.GetShipmentsByCustomerAsync(email)));

shipments.MapPost("/", async (ShipmentDto dto, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    var created = await service.CreateShipmentAsync(dto);
    return Results.Created($"api/shipments/track/{created.TrackingNumber}", created);
});

shipments.MapPut("/{id}/status", async (int id, StatusUpdateRequest request, IShipmentService service) =>
{
    await service.UpdateShipmentStatusAsync(id, request.Status);
    return Results.NoContent();
});
```

Also add a simple record at the bottom of Program.cs (or in a separate file):
```csharp
public record StatusUpdateRequest(string Status);
```

### 8. Register services in Client Program.cs

Edit `ShipmentTracker.Client/Program.cs` to register HttpClient and the shipment service:

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Hosting;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);

builder.Services.AddAuthorizationCore();
builder.Services.AddCascadingAuthenticationState();
builder.Services.AddAuthenticationStateDeserialization();

builder.Services.AddScoped(sp => new HttpClient { BaseAddress = new Uri(builder.HostEnvironment.BaseAddress) });
builder.Services.AddScoped<IShipmentService, ShipmentHttpService>();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();
```

### 9. Create the Dispatcher Dashboard page

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Pages/Dashboard.razor`:

```razor
@page "/dashboard"
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models
@using ShipmentTracker.Client.Services
@attribute [Authorize]
@inject IShipmentService ShipmentService

<PageTitle>Dispatcher Dashboard</PageTitle>

<h1>Dispatcher Dashboard</h1>

<div class="mb-3 row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
        <input class="form-control" placeholder="Filter by destination..." @bind="filterText" @bind:event="oninput" />
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <select class="form-select" @bind="statusFilter">
            <option value="">All Statuses</option>
            <option value="Pending">Pending</option>
            <option value="PickedUp">Picked Up</option>
            <option value="InTransit">In Transit</option>
            <option value="OutForDelivery">Out for Delivery</option>
            <option value="Delivered">Delivered</option>
            <option value="Exception">Exception</option>
        </select>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-3">
        <button class="btn btn-primary" @onclick="ShowCreateForm">+ New Shipment</button>
    </div>
</div>

@if (showCreateForm)
{
    <div class="card mb-3">
        <div class="card-body">
            <h5>Create New Shipment</h5>
            <div class="row g-2">
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <input class="form-control" placeholder="Origin" @bind="newShipment.Origin" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <input class="form-control" placeholder="Destination" @bind="newShipment.Destination" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <input class="form-control" placeholder="Customer Email" @bind="newShipment.CustomerEmail" />
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-3">
                    <input type="date" class="form-control" @bind="newShipment.EstimatedDelivery" />
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-2">
                <button class="btn btn-success btn-sm" @onclick="CreateShipment">Create</button>
                <button class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" @onclick="() => showCreateForm = false">Cancel</button>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
}

@if (shipments is null)
{
    <p>Loading shipments...</p>
}
else
{
    <table class="table table-striped">
        <thead>
            <tr>
                <th>Tracking #</th>
                <th>Origin</th>
                <th>Destination</th>
                <th>Status</th>
                <th>Customer</th>
                <th>Est. Delivery</th>
                <th>Actions</th>
            </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
            @foreach (var s in FilteredShipments)
            {
                <tr>
                    <td>@s.TrackingNumber</td>
                    <td>@s.Origin</td>
                    <td>@s.Destination</td>
                    <td><span class="badge bg-@GetStatusColor(s.Status)">@s.Status</span></td>
                    <td>@s.CustomerEmail</td>
                    <td>@s.EstimatedDelivery?.ToString("MMM dd, yyyy")</td>
                    <td>
                        <select class="form-select form-select-sm" value="@s.Status"
                            @onchange="e => UpdateStatus(s, e.Value?.ToString() ?? s.Status)">
                            <option value="Pending">Pending</option>
